  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role Overview</strong></p><p>Lead Out-of-Box Failures (OOBF) and cost-down projects at the Singapore manufacturing site. Drive cross-functional execution, ensure timely delivery, and maintain alignment with global stakeholders.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>• <strong>Planning & Execution</strong></p><p>o Develop and manage integrated plans for OOBF and cost-down initiatives.</p><p>o Develop and Maintain schedule, and budget; manage change control.</p><p>• <strong>Cross-Functional Coordination</strong></p><p>o Collaborate with Systems, ME/EE, Manufacturing, and Quality teams to implement solutions.</p><p>o Identify cost-down opportunities and track savings.</p><p>• <strong>Stakeholder Management</strong></p><p>o Act as single point of contact for client; prepare executive updates materials.</p><p>o Facilitate governance calls and maintain transparent communication.</p><p>• Compliance & Financials</p><p>o Ensure adherence to client QMS and safety protocols.</p><p>o Monitor budget and burn rate; support rate card and contracting processes.</p><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><p>• 7 to 10 years of proven project management experience in engineering environments.</p><p>• Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills.</p><p><strong>Preferred:</strong></p><p>• Exposure to Systems/ME/EE engineering.</p><p>• Experience with supplier cost-down and DFM/DFA practices.</p><p>• Familiarity with regulated environments (ISO 13485/FDA QSR).</p><p>• Background in RCA/CAPA and cost-down delivery.</p>",
